race.comment: MISS CHARMED (2) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a half a length second over 350m this track in 19.55. Top chance in this line up. MAC AND CHEESE (3) turned spotting a big start finishing eighth (23.38) last time in a Grade 5 at Geelong. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. ALL IN OLLIE (1) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.5 lengths (19.61) behind Greta's Gold at this track. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with five wins from seven starts. Leading chance. HOW AMAZING (8) cannot be dismissed although new to this venue.
